ge-old phenomena of literary multilingualism and translation on the part of writers and readers alike. In case studies of contemporary novels by Rabih Alameddine, Olga Grushin, Olga Grjasnowa, Michael Idov, Zinaida Lindén, Andreï Makine, and Eugene Vodolazkin, as well as a new look at Leo Tolstoy's nineteenth-century classic War and Peace, this book shows how reading can become a translingual process.  afunded by The Department of Modern Languages at Uppsala University  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Comparative Literature.2bisacsh  aliterary multilingualism, translingualism, translation, code-switching, heterographics, Tolstoy, War and Peace, contemporary fiction.2 aThe Department of Modern Languages at Uppsala Universityefunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAcademic Studies Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311102354008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAcademic Studies Press Complete eBook-Package 2024z978311143260108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2023 Part 2z978311117804208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2024 Part 2z978311133238340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9798887193861zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9798887193861zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9798887193861/original  a978-3-11-102354-0 Academic Studies Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-117804-2 DG Plus PP Package 2023 Part 2b2023  a978-3-11-133238-3 DG Plus PP Package 2024 Part 2b2024  a978-3-11-143260-1 Academic Studies Press Complete eBook-Package 2024b2024  aGBV-de